,Recommended,262940,26637477,"Posted: 16 November, 2016",all,heybabyxxx,"I loved the original game and none of the sequels impressed me as much. This fifth installment of the series tries to recapture the magic of that first masterpiece, bringing american George Stobbart (now working for an insurance company) and french journalist Nico Collard together again in lovely Paris for another adventure involving a religious cult and an old supernatural mystery, in several locations of Europe and the Middle East.But, besides the jokes involving goats, some recurring characters and good old George (voiced by Rolf Saxon) showing all the bizarre things he keeps in his pockets to everyone, this game lacks the amazing sense of humor of the original. It's not a bad point & click adventure (although the pixel hunting has become tiresome) and it's better than the 3rd game in 3D (I didn't play the 4th, considered the worst), but don't expect it to be as unforgettable as ""The Shadow of the Templars""."
