76561198084819662,Recommended,262940,16877671,"Posted: 4 July, 2015",all,pauldiazberrio,"An engaging, but short adventure. The Broken Sword games as a whole have been compelling and number five offers many  thrills, much humor  and suspense, albeit in a small package. A few more locales and characters to interact with would have made this installment better. The hand drawn illustrations are some of the best I have seen in a modern game, if not rather unexpected in the digital age. The dialogue is both funny and charismatic. The mystery of the murders, the Tabula Veritatis and the ancient connection to Jehovah and Lucifer are interesting and may appeal to members of gnostic and catholic faiths.The ending is good, but brief. If George and Nico's outing had been shown, it would have been a satisfying finale. As the conclusion is, it leaves players wanting more, but also wishing the story had lasted longer.All in all, Broken Sword 5 is a fine game, worthy of praise, but a little lacking in depth. What it offers is interesting, but if the game had had a little more depth, it could have been as notable as the first."
